if anyone has read the book the secret by rhonda byrne can you tell me if it actually worked for you i'm just curious to see if anybody had any results with it i tried it and nothing happened for me i wanted to know if it was just me or a big hoax the author recommends starting off small by visualizing little things coming to you like getting the parking space you wanted when the lots are full and that sort of thing before you visualize getting that dollar check in the mail so i tried that and the parking spaces thing actually worked instead of thinking i'll never find a spot in this crowded lot i thought i'll find a space right away and it worked so far i'm still doing the little visualizations i'm not picturing myself getting a check in the mail just yet will it continue to work i can't say for sure but i don't think it hurts to think more positively about things good luck and happy reading to you Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Theory of conduct Shaggy dog story Social rule Comment Voynich manuscript A Day in the Life April Fool's Day Care Bears Alcoholics Anonymous Jon Secada Extreme Programming Will Eisner Sydney Riot of 1879 Piccolo Junior Saga Hash table Theodore Kaczynski Mid-levels Baroque chess Sharon Tate CPU cache Satchel Paige Marilyn Monroe Lauren Bacall RuneScape quests Chess strategy and tactics Wheel of Fortune Bat Lash Good Times Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Pitaten Fantastic Four Anthroposophy Legal research Carl Barks San Francisco 49ers EastEnders The Emancipation of Mimi Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism XML John Byrne Oh My Goddess! The Cyberiad Open access Milgram experiment Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority 1957 World Series Interactive fiction Visual Basic Diving Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe The Price Is Right Philosophical skepticism Humphrey Bogart Bogdanov Affair Emacs United States Postal Service The Catcher in the Rye Grunge music Star Trek Customizable Card Game Ha